What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Flat Glass Market?
Market Analysis and Size
The flat glass market includes both coated and uncoated glass types. Coated flat glass features products like low-emissivity (Low-E) glass, which provides improved thermal insulation. Uncoated flat glass encompasses standard float glass, commonly used in windows and mirrors. Each type serves distinct applications, ranging from energy-efficient building facades to automotive windshields.
Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global flat glass market is expected to reach USD 22,41,66,817.79 thousand by 2031, which is 12,75,77,342.40 thousand in 2023, registering a CAGR of 7.3% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.
